      "content": "i see what u mean, but u didnt really answer the question of whether their reasoning is actually sound. like, if you look at the textualist approach vs the living constitution approach, one is grounded in the actual text and history, while the other is more about evolving social norms. wouldn't you say that the originalist method is more intellectually consistent for a judge to use?",
